MS-bashing:
----------

This was only when the opportunity presented itself, btw--he didn't go out
of his way to beat on Bill.  He was pretty gleeful when the opportunity *did*
arise, however. :-)

 - He mentioned that most ATMs run OS/2.  "I bet Bill's thinking about that
   whenever he goes to get some money."  (or something to that effect)

 - He went into a bookstore to buy the Unauthorized Win95 book ("for fuel"--
   it is *not* a pretty picture, by all accounts).  The guy at the counter
   said "Windows 95--what a stupid name!"  David's response:  "Yeah!" (lots
   of body language), and his first-ever tip to a bookstore employee.  Gotta
   love it...

 - MS said it would be impossible to get Windoze to run under OS/2, and then
   IBM did it.  Apparently they had the same problem with NT, because the
   Windoze running there is EMULATION licensed from Insignia (the SoftPC and
   SoftWin folks).  Hee hee...apparently for MS programmers it *is* an im-
   possibility, even owning all components of the code.  Smirk.

 - Bill Gates went Down Under to give some big keynote speech.  Unfortunately
   (for him), he picked the same day as the Pope.  Oooops...

 - Bill's bad day didn't end then, because someone in the diminished audience
   asked what his response was to Osborne's announcement.  For those who
   don't know, Osborne is Australia's biggest computer distributor, and they
   just announced that they are no longer distributing any Microsoft products.
   Instead they will load their systems only with IBM DOS 7 and IBM OS/2.
   Time to down a few dozen Fosters', eh, Bill?

